title: Teen stabbing, helicopter disaster evidence revealed | 7NEWS
description: A 15-year-old boy has handed himself in to police after fatally stabbing a 17-year-old at a reserve in Rouse Hill, Sydney's northwest. Meanwhile, new video evidence from the 2022 Gold Coast helicopter disaster that killed four people has been released at the coroner's inquest, revealing the catastrophic mid-air collision in chilling detail. One Nation leader Pauline Hanson was suspended from the Senate for wearing a burka in the chamber as part of a stunt to promote her bill banning face coverings. title: Teen charged with murder after fatal Rouse Hill stabbing | 7NEWS
description: A 15-year-old boy has been charged with murder after allegedly stabbing a 17-year-old boy in the leg at a reserve in Rouse Hill, Sydney's northwest. The victim was treated by paramedics at the scene but could not be saved, and the alleged attacker handed himself into police the following night. Police are seeking another person who may have information about the fatal stabbing, which occurred after school hours and was witnessed by students. title: Pauline Hanson suspended after burka stunt | 7NEWS
description: One Nation leader Pauline Hanson wore a burka into the Senate chamber while attempting to pass a private member's bill banning face coverings, resulting in her suspension by senators from across the political spectrum. The Queensland senator's actions, described as a repeat of a similar 2017 stunt, drew widespread condemnation from the Greens, Labour, Coalition and crossbench senators who voted to suspend her for one and a half hours. title: Gold Coast helicopter disaster footage revealed | 7NEWS
description: New video footage of the Gold Coast helicopter disaster that killed four people almost three years ago has been released during a coroner's inquest. The mid-air collision occurred just 23 seconds after takeoff, with investigators identifying multiple safety failures including five previous near misses in 90 days, faulty radio equipment, and inadequate safety briefings. title: Cyclonic storms devastate Bribie Island | 7NEWS
description: Severe storms with relentless rain and hail have caused cyclonic-level damage across southeast Queensland, with Bribie Island off Moreton Bay being the worst affected area. Huge trees have been uprooted and snapped, cars have been flipped, and roofs have been ripped off homes. Local residents describe it as the worst storm they have ever experienced on the island, with some reporting tornado-like conditions and funnel clouds touching down. title: Users change profile pictures in solidarity for South African women | 7NEWS
description: South African non-profit organisation tackling gender-based violence and femicide, Women For Change, urged women to participate in a global shutdown on November 21. The protest was staged intentionally a day before the G20 summit held in Johannesburg.   According to the United Nations Women, South Africa has one of the world's highest levels of femicide and gender-based violence rates, estimating that its five times higher than the global average.
